duration_ms = 10

    freqs, duration_ms, sample_rate=SR, n_classes=C, f=np.linalg.norm, snapshot_path=None)

trained_examples, trained_freq_activations = wavenet_features.generate_activations(
    freqs, duration_ms, sample_rate=SR, n_classes=C, f=np.linalg.norm,
    snapshot_path='snapshots/chromatic_2022-06-30_14-45-48')

n_layers = 30

subplot_aspect = 0.2
fig_width = 9
fig_height = n_layers * subplot_aspect * fig_width
fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_layers, 2, dpi=100, figsize=(fig_width, fig_height))
axes[0, 0].set_title('Untrained WaveNet')
axes[0, 1].set_title('WaveNet trained on chromatic scale (A$_3$ to A$_4$)')

for layer_id, ax_row in enumerate(axes):
    for ax in ax_row:
        if layer_id == n_layers - 1:
            ax.set_xlabel('Prefix frequency (Hz)')
        else:
            ax.set_xlabel('')

        ax.set_xticks(freqs[::2])
        ax.set_yticks([])
    ax_row[0].set_ylabel(f'Norm of layer {layer_id + 1}\nactivations')
    
    for col_id, ax in enumerate(ax_row):
        freq_activations = [untrained_freq_activations, trained_freq_activations][col_id]
        response = freq_activations[:, layer_id]
        ax.plot(freqs, response, '.-')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
